article.description: Canisius coasts to 64-50 win over Fairfield
article.headline: Canisius coasts to 64-50 win over Fairfield
article.linkText: Canisius coasts to 64-50 win over Fairfield
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. -- Phil Valenti scored 14 points and Josiah Heath and Kassius Robertson added 11 apiece to lead Canisius in a 64-50 victory over Fairfield on Thursday night. Canisius closed the opening half with five-straight points to lead 30-23, and opened the second with a 7-0 run to lead by double digits with 17:40 remaining. The Stags (6-13, 4-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) could get no closer than eight points the rest of the way. Robertson scored eight-straight points -- including back-to-back 3's -- to put the Griffins up by 16 points with 10:33 left to play. His 11 points were a career high. Valenti shot 5 of 10 from the floor and had nine rebounds. Jamal Reynolds added 10 points for the Griffins (11-7, 6-3). Marcus Gilbert finished with 18 points, 12 of those in the second half, and was the only Fairfield player to score in double figures.
